 {"id":"franken_numpy-k052","title":"Fix output dtype widening: narrow integer/float dtypes report as f64","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:23:37.846990482Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T03:29:10.701391689Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T03:29:10.700972385Z","close_reason":"Not a code bug: was a fixture encoding issue. DType::parse uses NumPy itemsize notation where i8=int64 and u8=uint64. Fixed fixtures to use 'uint8' and 'int8' instead. All narrow dtype cases now match correctly.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dtype","parity"],"comments":[{"id":25,"issue_id":"franken_numpy-k052","author":"ubuntu","text":"Values stored as Vec<f64> so U8+I8 promoted to I16 reports F64. Affected: u8_plus_i8, u8_plus_i16, f16_plus_u8. Fix: downcast to promoted dtype or migrate to ArrayStorage.","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:24:07Z"}]}
-{"id":"franken_numpy-k0xr","title":"PORT: numpy.fft __all__ order and namespace parity","description":"Reality-check gap: numpy.fft.__all__ is NumPy's ordered public list of 18 FFT helpers. fnp_python.fft currently installs the helper attributes but sets __all__ from a local tuple/order and only lazily resolves test. Align fnp_python.fft.__all__ with numpy.fft.__all__ exactly, preserve callable-module behavior for fnp_python.fft(...), and add conformance coverage for __all__ order plus identity/existence of every public helper.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T08:18:38.550011196Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T08:19:58.969660919Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fft","parity","python"]}
